tem performance at the same time.<br></li><li>Various options to tweak quality and performance exist to make widgets suit your needs. <br></li><li>As a general rule of thumb, static based widgets will perform best, while full animations widgets will require more resources from your system. <br></li><li>A dedicated GPU is highly recommended, but not required.</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >FAQ</h2>Q: How to config shortcuts in widget?<br>A: Please right click widget and select menuitem \"Settings...\"<br><br>Q: How to change widget size or zoom in/out widget?<br>A: Please right click widget and select menuitem \"Window > Zoom\"<br><br>Q: How to change widget Opacity?<br>A: Please right click widget and select menuitem \"Window > Opacity\"<br><br>Q: How to create widget?<br>A: Right click the tray icon of RainWidget and select the menu item \"Create Widget\",it will auto create a simple widget from template and run it on your desktop,and it will auto open the folder of the widget and list all the widget's files e.g. HTML CSS JS , you can edit the files and then click the widget and select menu item \"Refresh\" or press F5 to update widget.",
